                    <p class=MsoTitleCxSpFirst style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=TR
                    style='font-size:18.0pt;color:#002060'>Protection of Personal Data</span></b></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoTitleCxSpLast style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR
                    style='font-size:24.0pt;color:#002060'>Website Visitors / Cookie Information
                    Text</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR>&nbsp;</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times New Roman",serif;color:#002060'>According to the Personal Data
                    Protection Law No. 6698 (&quot;Law&quot;), ARAS İNŞAAT TİCARET TURİZM ANONİM
                    ŞİRKETİ (&quot;Hereinafter referred to as 'PORT NATURE'&quot;) is defined as
                    the data controller due to processing personal data about you. According to
                    Article 10 of the Law titled &quot;Obligation to Inform&quot;, data controllers
                    are obliged to inform the real persons whose personal data they process on certain
                    issues.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=TR
                    style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#002060'>Relevant Person</span></b><span
                    lang=TR style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#002060'>: You, whose
                    personal data we process through cookies and different identifiers because you
                    visit our website in the [https://portnature.com.tr/] domain, are defined as
                    the relevant person by the Law.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=TR
                    style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#002060'>Data Controller</span></b><span
                    lang=TR style='font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:#002060'>: [PORT NATURE]
                    is the data controller who determines the purposes and means of processing
                    personal data regarding personal data about you and is responsible for
                    establishing and managing the data recording system</span><span lang=TR
                    style='font-family:"Times",serif;color:#002060'>.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=TR
                    style='font-family:"Times",serif;color:#002060'>INFORMATION ABOUT COOKIES;</span></b></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>However, we process some of your personal data
                    through cookies on our site.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>Cookies refer to technologies such as advertising
                    IDs and web identifiers (all of these technologies will be referred to as
                    &quot;Cookies&quot;).</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><i><span lang=TR
                    style='font-family:"Times",serif;color:#002060'>What is Cookie?</span></i></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>Cookies are very small text files, usually consisting
                    of letters and numbers, that are saved on your computer (or other devices such
                    as a smartphone or tablet) via browsers by the websites you visit. Cookies
                    allow the user and his device to be recognized and to store some information
                    about the user's preferences and past transactions. Cookies are created by the
                    servers that manage the website you visit. This way, the server can understand
                    when the visitor visits the same site. Cookies can be likened to ID cards that
                    show website owners that the same visitor has visited the site again.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>For more detailed information about cookies, you
                    can visit https://www.aboutcookies.org/ and https://www.allaboutcookies.org/.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>Obtaining Personal Data Through Cookies</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>When you first visit our website, you will be presented
                    with a screen regarding your cookie preferences. Depending on the cookies you
                    allow to be used on this screen, the relevant cookies are stored on your
                    browser/device. Each cookie typically contains the following elements:</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>• The server to which the cookie is sent,</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>• Predetermined lifespan of the cookie,</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>• A unique identifying value/number, usually
                    randomly generated (the website server sending the cookie uses this value to
                    recognize you when you navigate between pages).</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>Data is collected by completely automatic methods
                    through cookies. Cookies can be classified according to their owners, lifetime
                    and purposes of use:</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>• Depending on the owner, cookies are used,
                    first-party cookies placed on your device by the website you visit and
                    third-party cookies served by third parties. While primary cookies are offered
                    by PORT NATURE, third party cookies are offered by different companies that
                    receive service or are business partners.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>• Depending on their lifetime, session cookies and
                    persistent cookies are used. While session cookies are deleted when the visitor
                    leaves the website, persistent cookies are stored on visitors' devices for a
                    predetermined lifetime and are used to remember the visitor and his preferences
                    on his next visit.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>• Depending on their intended use, strictly
                    necessary cookies, analytical cookies and targeting/advertising cookies are
                    used on the site.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><i><span lang=TR
                    style='font-family:"Times",serif;color:#002060'>Data Collected Through Cookies,
                    Purposes of Use and Legal Reasons</span></i></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>Data regarding user transaction records are
                    collected and processed through cookies; the browser and operating system you
                    use, IP address, user ID, date and time of your visit, access status, use of
                    features on the website, search phrases you enter, how often you visit our
                    website, your language preferences, actions you perform on the pages.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>Cookies are used for the following purposes;
                    Ensuring that your visit to our website and your experience there are stable
                    and that your information is remembered the next time you use it, improving the
                    operation and content of the site, statistically evaluating site usage, presenting
                    the content on the site in the most effective way for you and your device and
                    offering users customized services and advertisements in line with their
                    preferences and usage habits. Cookies are divided into various categories
                    according to their purpose of use and functions. Below, the cookies used on our
                    website according to their categories, the providers of the cookies, the
                    foreign countries to which personal data may be transferred through cookies,
                    and the purposes and legal reasons for use of each cookie are listed:</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=TR
                    style='font-family:"Times",serif;color:#002060'>1. Mandatory Cookies</span></b></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>These are cookies that are necessary for the use
                    and functionality of the website. If mandatory cookies are disabled, access to
                    part or all of the site may not be possible. Personal data processed through
                    mandatory cookies are processed because data processing is mandatory for the
                    establishment, use or protection of a right stipulated in KVKK Article 5/2e,
                    for the purposes of offering products and services and carrying out activities
                    in accordance with the legislation.</span></p>
                    
                    <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=TR style='font-family:
                    "Times",serif;color:#002060'>Mandatory cookies used on our website, their
                    providers and purposes of use are as follows:</span></p>
                    
